         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ Sir, — In answer to an inquiry contained in  ¶ The Argus ¶  of this date, ¶  I beg to mention that the  ¶ Alantus glandulosa ¶ , ¶  which furnishes food to a new and hardy kind of silkworm, has bee...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">61.04.24</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To the Editor of the Argus</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found. For the text given here, see 'Silkworms', <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 26 April 1861, p. 5 (B61.04.05). The letter was reprinted in the<seg style="font-style: italic; "> Star</seg> (Ballarat), 27 April 1861, p. 2 (B61.04.10).</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir, — In answer to an inquiry contained in <seg style="font-style: italic; ">The Argus</seg> of this date,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 24 April 1861, p. 7, for a letter signed 'A Constant Reader', of Geelong, inquiring as to whether <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Ailanthus glandulosus</seg> had yet been brought to the colony.</p>
               </note> I beg to mention that the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Alantus%20glandulosa">Alantus glandulosa</name>
               </seg>,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Ailanthus glandulosa</seg>?</p>
               </note> which furnishes food to a new and hardy kind of silkworm, has been extensively distributed from this garden during the last season, and that plants of this valuable tree are again available this year.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Since the plant may be readily multiplied by division of the roots, no difficulty exists of rendering soon on any estate an ample supply of the tree available for the rearing of its peculiar bombyx.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Most respectfully yours,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>FERD. MUELLER.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne Botanic and Zoological Gardens,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">April 24.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Alantus%20glandulosa">Alantus glandulosa</name>
            </p>
